article.headline: Cent. Connecticut St. 82, Lafayette 78
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. -- Ken Horton scored 20 points and added seven rebounds as Central Connecticut State defeated Lafayette 82-78 on Sunday. Horton hit a pair of free throws with 58.2 seconds left to put Central ahead 77-75. Jared Mintz hit one of two at the line with 33.5 seconds to play to pull the Leopards (2-4) within one, and Shemik Thompson scored three seconds later to make it 78-76 for the Blue Devils. Thompson forced a jump ball on the next possession, and CCSU took the ball on the possession arrow. He then made two at the line to ice the game for Central (2-3). Thompson had 11 assists for Central, which got 18 points from freshman Robby Ptacek and eight points and nine boards from David Simmons. Lafayette scored the first seven points of the second half to take a 46-43 lead, but Central didn't let the Leopards pull away. Jeff Kari led the Leopards with 23 points while Andrew Brown added 16.
